            <entry xml:id="entry_arǧævnæ" xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>arǧævnæ</orth></form>
                <usg><lang/></usg>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>клещи</q>
                    </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">; и. <ref type="xr"
                            target="#entry_arkʼaw"/></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">; Iron
                            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arkʼaw"/></note><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>pliers</q>
                    </abv:tr><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">; и. <ref type="xr"
                            target="#entry_arkʼaw"/></note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">; Iron
                            <ref type="xr" target="#entry_arkʼaw"/></note></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>alli brigadæmæ dær ǧæwama wa... æmpʼozægi mænkʼæj arǧævnitæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>every brigade should have... little repair pliers</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q/>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"
                            /><biblScope>245%l3%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ʒæbokæ æ razmæ, arǧævnæ.....</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>перед ним молоток, клещи...</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>before him there is a hammer, pliers...</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_AK"/><biblScope>II 32</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <w type="rec">agrab(a)na-</w>; ср. по образованию д.
                        <ref type="xr" target="#entry_araznæ"/> ‘руль’ (от <w>arazun</w> [<ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_arazyn"/>] ‘направлять’), д. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_izaznæ"/> ‘лом’ (от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_izazun"/>),
                    д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xeznæ"/> ‘пастбище’ (от <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_xezun"/> ‘пасти’), д. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_færæznæ"
                    /> ‘возможность’ (от %ifærazun%i [<ref type="xr" target="#entry_færazyn"/>]
                    ‘мочь’) и др. Основа <w>rǧæv-</w> представляет закономерное развитие из
                    %i*grab-%i (%igr%i → %irg%i, ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cyrǧ"/>), эта же
                    основа налична в и. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7rǧævyn"/> ‘взваливать
                    (ношу)’, д. %iærǧævun%i ‘схватывать’, ‘попадать в цель’, а также, с другой
                    огласовкой, в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lǧīvyn"/>, %ilqīvyn%i | %iʽlqevun%i
                    ‘сжимать’. Общеиндоевропейская основа %i*ghre(i)bh-%i ‘хватать’, ‘сгребать’ и
                    пр. обильно представлена в индоиранских, славянских, балтийских и германских
                    языках, причем нередко в названиях орудий, например <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*aγraβan(ʼγrβn)</w>
                        <gloss><q>вилы</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>щипцы</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>grābhá-, grabhana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>орудие хватания</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>рукоять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>грабли</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>greblȳs</w>
                        <gloss><q>грабли</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>grāp</w>
                        <gloss><q>кулак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>коготь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>greifa</w>
                        <gloss><q>вилы</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Griff</w></mentioned>. Дальнейшие соответствия см. под <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7rǧævyn"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lǧīvyn"
                            />.<lb/><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>574</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Goes back to %i*agrab(a)na-%i; for derivation, cf. <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_araznæ"/> ‘steering wheel’ (from %iarazun%i [<ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_arazyn"/>] ‘direct’), Digor <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_izaznæ"/> ‘pinch-bar’ (from <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_izazun"/>), Digor <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xeznæ"/>
                    ‘pasture’ (from <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xezun"/> ‘graze’), Digor <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_færæznæ"/> ‘possibility’ (from %ifærazun%i [<ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_færazyn"/>] ‘be able’) etc. The stem %irǧæv-%i
                    regularly developed from %i*grab-%i (%igr%i → %irg%i, cf. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cyrǧ"/>), the same stem is availaible in Iron <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7rǧævyn"/> ‘load (carry)’, Digor %iærǧævun%i ‘grab’, ‘hit the
                    mark’ and also (with other vocalization) <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lǧīvyn"
                    />, %ilqīvyn%i | %iʽlqevun%i ‘squeeze’. The common Indo-European stem
                    %i*ghre(i)bh-%i ‘grab’, ‘rake’ etc. abundantly represented in Indo-Iranian,
                    Slavic, Baltic and Germanic languages, often in the names of weapons, for
                    example, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*aγraβan(ʼγrβn)</w>
                        <gloss><q>hayfork</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>forceps</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>grābhá-, grabhana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>grasping tool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>handle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>грабли</w>
                        <gloss><q>rake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lt"><lang/>
                        <w>greblȳs</w>
                        <gloss><q>rake</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><lang/>
                        <w>grāp</w>
                        <gloss><q>fist</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ang"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>claw</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="goh"><lang/>
                        <w>greifa</w>
                        <gloss><q>hayfork</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Griff</w></mentioned>. For further correspondences, see <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_7rǧævyn"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_7lǧīvyn"
                            />.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>574</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
